                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus>
                    blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="003"> f. 1r (and passim)</locus>
                    mentions an owner Śahǝl ʾƎgziʾäbǝḥer (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሣህለ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    Some of the text where one would expect red ink has been written in green ink (i.e. <locus target="#71v #81v" facs="074 084">Fols. 71v, 81v</locus>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#76v" facs="079">Fol. 76v</locus>
                    mentions Ḫaylä ʾIyyäsus (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ኃይለ፡ ኢየሱስ፡</foreign>). This may be the name of the scribe
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#134v" facs="137">Fol. 134v</locus>
                    scrawls in blue ink
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    The book has been foliated with blue stamped numbers in the lower recto corner
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#127v" facs="130">Fol. 127v</locus>
                    4 x 4 grid with play on ʾÄnanya (<foreign xml:lang="gez">አናንያ፡</foreign>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#54 #84 #117" facs="056 086 119">Fols. 54, 84, 117</locus>
                    red string stitched into fore edge of folio as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#90 #108" facs="092 110">Fols. 90, 108</locus>
                    green string stitched into fore edge of folio as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#102 #127" facs="104 129">Fols. 102, 127</locus>
                    yellow string stitched into fore edge of folio as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e9">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#134" facs="136">Fol. 134</locus>
                    black and green string stitched into fore edge of folio as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e10">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 6–16 have numbers and/or headings
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e11">
                    <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#3r #6v #7r #14r #16v" facs="004 009 016 019">folss. 3r, 6v, 7r, 14r, 16v, </locus>, etc.);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#14r #19r #26r #27v #88r" facs="016 021 028 030 090">14r, 19r, 26r, 27v, 88r, </locus>, etc.);
                      text has been removed (<locus target="#9r #16r #35v #59r #79v" facs="011 018 038 061 082">9r, 16r, 35v, 59r, 79v</locus>, etc.)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
